A great new motion pictuse based he
Fulton Oursler's
bestseller,
"The
Greatest Story Ever Told", is now being
produced by
George Stevens Produc-
tions, Inc. and United Artists.
The sets
for this film are among the largest ever
erected in California. They entail a rep-
lica of the central section of old Jerusa-
lem,
and
there
are
many
other huge
sound stages representing familiar Bib-
lical locales.
Among the featured players are John
Wayne, Sidney Poitier, Charlton Heston
and Max Von Sydow. Carl Sandburg
collaborated on the script, and George
Stevens, twice an Academy Award Win-
ner, is Producer/Director.
From September 4 through April 30,
1963, these tours will leave at 9:00 AM,
10:30 AM, 2:00 PM and 3:30 PM from
9336 West Washington Boulevard, Cul-

on the picture. A souvenir brochure is
available for each visitor.
American Airlines passengers-twelve
years of age and older—travelling in or
out of Los Angeles may pick up their
free tickets—at least 24 hours in advance
-at the American Airlines "Will Call"
desk at Los Angeles International Air-
port, or at all American Airlines ticket
offices.
